reviews.review_text: Thanks for the memories... My most "listened to" boot.  Almost as hot as I remember the show.  Maybe my most fave of all "Shakedown's".  And Brent was just smokin' (as was Jerry) on M&MU into Big River.
best sound out of the 5 different versions this sounds the best.

What a great show.  Happy Anniversary! As of today, 30 years later, this bootleg set the stage for one heck of a run. It was my first show and my favorite boot. I never saw one to top it. The Shakedown was enlightening, from the stage to the seats way in the back of Barton Hall.

First General Admission Show for me We arrived at the arena 2 hours before the doors opening only to find out that my brother and his frat bros had camped out the night before and were in the front of the line...nice!

Doors opened and we rushed to the front of the stage and enjoyed a solid first set up close and personal...during the intermission, the crowd pushed in so hard that we had to fight our way out, my GF at the time was sobbing, it was pretty bad...

Second set was spent in the bleachers off to the side, if you've never been to Barton Hall, it's pretty sparse, just an open floor with some bleachers on the sides.  Shakedown was awesome, the Black Peter solid, the Nobody's Fault But Mine, we were going crazy hoping Jerry would sing it, oh well, still a solid show in a memorable place
Choice AUD, for sure An excellent quality AUD.  Thanks
